{"key":"post-10983268","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10983268</id>\n<content>You can use perlite in casing layers, but most growers don't case, especially if growing cubensis.&amp;nbsp; However, whether you use it or not, perlite and vermiculite are not the same thing at all.&amp;nbsp; Perlite is like glass, being a crystalline mineral, and doesn't absorb water.&amp;nbsp; Vermiculite is like a mineral sponge, absorbing many times its weight in water.&amp;nbsp; Take a look at this thread which explains &lt;a href=&quot;/forums/showflat.php/Number/6610766#6610766&quot; class=&quot;pp&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;the difference between perlite and vermiculite.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10983418</next>\n<prev>10982899</prev>\n<first>10982788</first>\n<last>10983418</last>\n<when>1251866508</when>\n<utime>09/02/09 07:41 AM</utime>\n</post>"}